values: certain days when im just floating about and this is one. i have no idea what happened up until this moment (well i do, MY bLUD JONBABY SAID WASSAP @ THE UNION) and now i need to nap for a good 40 minutes before class. eeeicky. i could use home right about now. =[

So yay for weekend fast approaching, nay for Calc exam tuesday, and yay for paintballing. I hope that last one's a yay at least. I'm all for paintballing online (Quake), but if this kind is going to turn into udayan-threshing...NO. At least it's another excuse to visit Davis again, which I thoroughly enjoyed last weekend. Dex and the closet hospitality made me a stronger person, resistant to as many gay jokes as you can dish out. If you smile at a boy, tell them you're from Frisco, you guarantee yourself problems. Oh well, I've changed to hometown San Mateo as Lynn requested..so YAY. 

I'm so confused as to why I'm not tired right now. I was zombieboy like two hours ago..GRRRR how come this shit never happens when I need it to. Let me see what Spring is like.

Wahooo for pushing myself to go to Calc. Cutie professor wasn't there but we had a decent substitute. When it's my favorite professor you're substituting for, you better bring the goods nah mean sucka. You could see the entire class become hostile toward her as she entered and starting giving us handouts, but a few inside jokes and she was quickly on our side. I almost snapped at her for asking why I was doing my notes instead of the assignment, but I keep forgetting this is college. IT AIN'T NONE OF HER DAMN BIZNEZ. I remember those traumatic days in the library where the mass-copying was a covert operation and we always had to tell the librarians that we were here on a field trip and it would be over shortly (actually, that was mine. what was yours? please post!)
